      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INSANE (3) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing second (22.76) and beaten 7 lengths over 390m at this track. Expected to feature in the finish again. MORAINE GRACE (2) was safely held in tougher company last start at Horsham, but prior to that won by 0.8 lengths at Ballarat (22.54) beating Diva's Rose in a Grade 5 on March 16. Should be in this for a long way. PENNY PINTO (6) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 2.25 lengths (23.72) at Horsham. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. BERT DEEDS (8) is a last start winner who can measure up again.",
